Passengers step into a bus on March 14, 2020 in Polokwane, in Limpopo province after disembarking from a South African Airways Airbus A340-600 plane carrying South African citizens who have been repatriated from Wuhan, China, where they were working when the novel coronavirus (COVID-19) erupted. JOHANNESBURG - The South Africans from Wuhan are home. The 146 South Africans arrived in Polokwane on Saturday amid the coronavirus outbreak in China. LIVESTREAM: South Africans from Wuhan arrive in Polokwane One of the citizens has expressed gratitude to the crew and penned a heartwarming letter. The group will be placed in quarantine for 21 days at The Ranch Resort. All passengers have been tested prior to the flight back from China, and none were positive for COVID-19. READ THE LETTER BELOW: